  "result": "The bell above the door chimed, a small, brassy sound that felt entirely out of place in the heavy morning fog. Inside the cafe, the air smelled of roasted espresso beans, old paper, and a faint hint of cinnamon. It was one of those forgotten places, sandwiched between a towering glass office building and an abandoned brick warehouse. \n\nI took a seat by the window, watching the city slowly wake up. A lone street sweeper hummed down the damp asphalt, pushing aside wet, auburn leaves. Inside, the barista, an older man with silver wire glasses, methodically wiped down the espresso machine. He moved with a practiced rhythm, treating the rusted metal with the reverence of a cathedral altar. \n\nThere is a profound comfort in being awake before the rest of the world. It feels like existing in a secret pocket of time, a rare parenthesis in the otherwise relentless sentence of daily life. Nobody expects anything of you at dawn. Your inbox is quiet, your phone screen remains dark, and the weight of impending obligations has not yet settled on your shoulders. \n\nI wrapped both hands around the warm ceramic mug, feeling the heat seep into my chilled fingers. The first sip was perfectly bitter, waking up my senses in an instant. Outside, the gray sky finally fractured, allowing a single, sharp ray of golden sunlight to pierce the gloom. The day had officially begun, but for just a few more peaceful moments, this quiet sanctuary belonged only to me.",
